text:
They're never one to shy away from a social media PDA.

And Victoria and David Beckham made sure to share one on one of the most special nights of the year, as they enjoyed a New Year's Eve kiss on Thursday.

Posted by the 40-year-old retired footballer on his oft-used Instagram page, the sweet image showed him puckering up to his wife as they kissed in front of a tree covered in fairy lights.

Scroll down for video

Besotted: David and Victoria Beckham prepared to ring in the New Year as the retired footballer shared a sweet PDA snap of the two of them on Instagram

Along with the snap, perhaps taken by one of their four children, the besotted gent gushed: 'And from us of course... Have an amazing 2016.'

The picture followed one of their children sat looking over the very same tree, taken from behind and merely showing the silhouettes of their heads keenly gazing at the pretty sight before them.

From left to right, the image showed Cruz, 10, next to Brooklyn, 16, then four-year-old Harper and Romeo, 13.

And their doting daddy added a message for his 17.7m Instagram followers: 'Happy new year from our beautiful babies.'

'Happy new year from our beautiful babies': The 40-year-old also shared a picture of their children - Cruz, 10, Brooklyn, 16, four-year-old Harper and Romeo, 13 - on Thursday

Celebrating! Brooklyn also shared a snap, celebrating Gordon Ramsay's twins' Jack and Holly's birthday

David and Victoria's loving smooch snap comes almost a week after their last: the sporting icon shared a similar photograph of the two kissing under the mistletoe, just before Christmas day.

He wrote: 'Kisses at Christmas are always the best ones... Kids took this picture of mum and dad obviously slightly @victoriabeckham @brooklynbeckham ... Merry Christmas.'

Although the destination of their festive getaway is unclear, they certainly looked as though they were having a jolly time of it - with even Victoria, 41, ditching her famous pout in favour of a wide smile as she posed with her husband and family in another snap.

Keeping it chic: On New Year's Eve, Victoria kept it simple, writing alongside a leopard print 2016 image - Thank u to everyone who has made this year so special. Looking forward to an amazing 2016 – Happy New Year fashion bunnies!

With the whole Beckham clan stood in front of a snowy scene, she added: 'Happy Christmas!! Lots of love from the Beckhams!!we love u!!' (sic).'

It has clearly been a fantastic festive season for the famous family, who appeared to be marking the end of 2015 with a bang.

The eldest of the Beckham children, Brooklyn, also got in on the social media sharing action as he posted a picture on Thursday, celebrating the birthday of his close friends Jack and Holly Ramsay, Gordon Ramsay's twins.

In the snap he was also joined by one of the TV chef's other children, daughter Megan, and he added: 'Happy birthday @jackramsay1999 @hollyramsayy. @megan__ramsay. Happy new year.'

'Kisses at Christmas': David and Victoria smooched under the mistletoe in a sweet snap the former football player uploaded to Instagram on Christmas Eve

Happy Christmas from the Beckhams! David, Victoria, Brooklyn, Romeo, Cruz and Harper offered fans a glimpse of their magical winter wonderland Christmas on Friday morning

Handsome elf: Victoria also posted a cute snap of David hanging out by a roaring fire over the Christmas period

The Beckhams have been keeping their millions of fans up to date with their festive antics over the past week, with both David and Victoria sharing pictures on their social media pages.

One of the most popular shots was shared by the former Spice Girl, showing her handsome husband clad in a Christmas jumper in front of a roaring fire.

She joked: 'Best Santa ever! #kissesfromthebeckhams X vb @davidbeckham @brooklynbeckham.'

Getting his own back! The father-of-four was pictured KO'd as the festivities of Christmas Day got on top of him, forcing him to take an impromptu nap, in this picture shared by Brooklyn

Cheeky: The eldest of the Beckham clan covered David in Quality Streets as he napped

Meanwhile, Brooklyn managed to get his own back on his cheeky dad - who had posted a picture of the teen with a Christmas elf beforehand - sharing snaps of him passed out on the sofa having a typical dad snooze at Christmas.

Not only that, but the prankster managed to cover his father with chocolates, placing them gently on his face and taking pictures for all the world to see.

'Got ya #kissesfromtheBeckhams,' he added with one snap, writing, 'Caught my dad asleep,' with another.
